      "amount": "1 tsp",
      "notes": "To balance flavors"
    },
    {
      "name": "Black Pepper",
      "amount": "1/4 tsp",
      "notes": "To add depth"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Roll out the pie crust and place in a 9-inch pie dish.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the Kenyan Cheese Blend, Gruyère Cheese, melted butter, eggs, salt, and black pepper. Mix well.",
    "Pour the cheese mixture into the pie crust.",
    "Bake for 35-40 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the filling is set.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool for 10 minutes before serving."
